section.p:
API2 is the original C 2.0 API, and is available in all versions of libcouchbase, but
                is considered deprecated since version 2.6.0. It looks something like
                this:lcb_get_cmd_t gcmd = { 0 };
lcb_get_cmd_t* gcmd_p = &gcmd;
gcmd.version = 0;
gcmd.v.v0.key = "key";
gcmd.v.v0.nkey = nkey;
lcb_get(instance, cookie, 1, &gcmd);
lcb_wait(instance);lcb_set_get_callback(get_callback);

void get_callback(lcb_t instance, const void *cookie, lcb_error_t err, const lcb_resp_get_t *resp)
{
    if (err) {
        // ...
    } else {
        printf("Value is: %.*s\n", (int)resp->v.v0.nbytes, resp->v.v0.bytes);
    }
}API3
                is available since version 2.5.6 (but see note below) and offers a more concise way
                of performing
                operations:lcb_CMDGET gcmd = { 0 };
LCB_CMD_SET_KEY(&gcmd, "key", 3);
lcb_get3(instance, cookie, &gcmd);lcb_install_callback(instance, LCB_CALLBACK_GET, (lcb_RESPCALLBACK)get_callback);

void get_callback(lcb_t instance, int cbtype, const lcb_RESPGET *resp)
{
    if (resp->rc) {
        //
    } else {
        printf("Value is: %.*s\n", (int)resp->nvalue, resp->value);
    }
}

p.note:
While API3 is available from version 2.4.0, the above example will only work
                    from version 2.5.6, although it will compile on any version. Versions prior to
                    2.5.6 require explicit scheduling to be used in the application. Explicit
                    scheduling requires invoking lcb_sched_enter() and
                        lcb_sched_leave() around any code scheduling operations.
                    Therefore the above snippet will work in version 2.4.0 and higher by using the
                    following:lcb_sched_enter(instance);
lcb_get3(instance, cookie, &gcmd);
lcb_sched_leave(instance);
